import Sidebar from '../../components/Sidebar.astro';
const title = "Kirk & Heavens (1989) - ArXiv Atlas";
import WikiLink from '../../components/WikiLink.astro';
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">Kirk &amp; Heavens (1989)</h1>

    <div class="stub-banner">⚠️ <strong>Stub</strong> — content pending analysis</div>

    <div class="infobox">
      <h3 class="infobox-title">Kirk & Heavens 1989</h3>
      <table>
        <tr><th>Type:</th><td>Paper</td></tr>
        <tr><th>DOI:</th><td><a href="https://doi.org/10.1086/166490">10.1086/166490</a></td></tr>
        <tr><th>Topic:</th><td>Particle acceleration at oblique shocks; guide-field effects on DSA</td></tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p><strong>Kirk &amp; Heavens (1989)</strong> studied particle acceleration at oblique shocks, demonstrating how the magnetic field orientation relative to the shock normal affects the acceleration efficiency and the resulting particle spectrum. This work is foundational for understanding DSA in geometries where the shock is not perpendicular to the upstream flow, as occurs at <WikiLink slug="pages/recollimation-shocks" text="recollimation shocks" />.</p>

    <h2>Relevance to ArXiv Atlas</h2>
    <p>Cited by <WikiLink slug="pages/2603.16647" text="Peretti et al. (2603.16647)" /> when discussing the limitations of their 1D model regarding oblique-shock physics and guide-field effects not fully captured in the current framework.</p>

    <h2>See also</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><WikiLink slug="pages/particle-acceleration-oblique-shocks" text="Particle acceleration — oblique shocks" /></li>
      <li><WikiLink slug="pages/diffusive-shock-acceleration" text="Diffusive shock acceleration" /></li>
      <li><WikiLink slug="pages/Bell2011" text="Bell (2011)" /></li>
    </ul>
  </main>
</Base>
